/system/ directory build instructions
=====================================

The /system/ directory available on the nemo platform and provided in prebuilt
form by android_nemo-ng.bb is a tricky mix of an original Android Wear /system
and some recompiled parts. This is due to the half-closed nature of Android
Wear. This file explains you how to rebuild manually your own /system dir.

The nemo ships Android 7.1.1 (build NWD1.180306.004, SDK 25). Either adb pull
from a live device or mount a system.img extracted from the device:

  # Option A: live device
  adb pull /system/ system

  # Option B: system.img
  sudo mount -o loop,ro system.img /mnt/nemo-system
  cp -r /mnt/nemo-system/ system

  cd system/
  rm -rf app/ fonts/ framework/ media/ priv-app/ xbin/
  sed -i "/persist.hwc.mdpcomp.enable=true/d" build.prop
  cd vendor/lib/egl/
  ln -s libGLESv2_adreno.so libGLESv2S3D_adreno.so
  cd ../../../lib/hw/
  ln -s hwcomposer.msm8226.so hwcomposer.nemo.so
  ln -s gralloc.msm8226.so gralloc.nemo.so
  ln -s memtrack.msm8226.so memtrack.nemo.so
  cd ../../vendor/lib/hw/
  ln -s sensors.msm8226.so sensors.nemo.so
  cd ../../../

Note: lights.nemo.so and power.nemo.so already exist as real files in the
Nougat dump and must not be replaced with symlinks.

This installation wouldn't be enough because libhybris needs a patched bionic
and some components need to be recompiled on the QCOM platform with the
QCOM_BSP flag. Thankfully, those specific parts are open-source so we can
download and then build them. (This may take a while)

  ### Download
  curl https://storage.googleapis.com/git-repo-downloads/repo > repo
  chmod a+x repo
  mkdir -p android-nemo-ng/
  cd android-nemo-ng
  ../repo init -u https://github.com/MagneFire/android_manifest \
               -b nougat-mr1.8-release
  ../repo sync

  ### Build (can only be done in bash)
  . build/envsetup.sh
  export TARGET_USES_C2D_COMPOSITION=true # Needed by copybit
  export TARGET_USES_QCOM_BSP=true        # Fixes GPU problems on QCOM platforms
  export TARGET_BOARD_PLATFORM=msm8226    # We specify the SoC by hand
  mmma hardware/qcom/display/msm8226/     # hwcomposer, gralloc, dependencies...
  mmma frameworks/native/cmds/servicemanager/
  mmma system/core/logd/
  mmma system/core/init/

  If you get an error like "linux/msm_kgsl.h: No such file or directory", edit
  hardware/qcom/display/msm8226/common.mk and add this line:

  common_includes += $(LOCAL_PATH)/../../../msm8x26/kernel-headers/

  ### Installation
  cp out/target/product/generic/root/init ../system/bin/
  cp -r out/target/product/generic/system/* ../system/

libhybris headers
=================

Skip this step. libhybris headers come from a separate version-pinned package
independent of the per-device system-dir tarball; see
meta-narwhal/conf/machine/narwhal.conf for how this is handled in the build
system.

With the system directory prepared, create the system-dir tarball:

  tar czf system-nougat-nemo.tar.gz system/
